review_blob: Bottle poured into a pint glass.  Aroma is pleasant, almost floral, with notes of malt and bread. Nice brown colour with a frothy head.  Almost creamy texture and soft carbonation.  Not as bitter as Samuel Adams Lager, but the flavour almost ends before you would like it to.  I would definitely buy this again.
Beautiful dense head, flavourful yet not overpowering. One of the better beers I have tried. I will be sampling more from Anchor soon!
Excellent Beer.  Prominent nut brown flavour, but not overwhelming.  Good balance, texture and colour.  One of my favourites.
Decent bitter beer.  Has a flavour similar to Guinness and I would not mind having it again on tap.
Can. Nothing special, goes down easy.  Much better on draught, has a strong hint of apples. Decent beer that I would not mind drinking again.

This is an easy drinking beer which I dont mind having now and then.  It has slight amount of flavour, but is a bit too watery.  This definitely should be had on tap.  Oh, and an excellent, lacy head.

Beautiful black colouration, with a great cherry mocha head.  Hints of dark chocolate, coffee, bit of oatmeal, and possibly some fruits.  This beer almost has a different scent every time you smell it.  Not a big fan of stouts, but this beer makes me appreciate them more.  Would love to try this on tap.
Decent and and average appearance, but this one goes down easy andhas just enough flavour to make you enjoy it.  A good beer that I would purchase again.

Bottle.  This beer has mild character, but is a bit one dimensional.  It has that irish ale hoppy bitterness and impressive dark brown hue, but not enough flavour to make it one of my regular brews.  Still, I would like to have this again.

Does anyone actually like this stuff (can't call it beer!)?  I can understand if you drink a certain beer A LOT, you might come to enjoy it but oh man is this bad!  Its so bad I rather have a Canadian.  Never again will I willingly let this touch my lips!
I enjoyed this beer from the tap.  It has a nice taste of wood or nuts, with a faint sweetness.  Not enough flavour, however, for me to call it excellent.  Disgusting metallic taste out of the can.
I heard good things about this beer but I was unimpressed.  Nice brown/amber colour and nutty aroma.  Sweet nutty taste in the beginning, but too much of a bitter finish for my liking.
This is like a dirty Corona.  It goes down easy but has a slight dirty/burnt taste to it.  I would drink it again but it's not worth the price.
A decent beer with somewhat of a wheat flavour.  Easy on the palate and goes down smooth.  I would not mind trying it again.
UPDATED: APR 14, 2004

It might be the fact that i dont drink beer like this, but i thought this "brew" was horrible. It was like i was drinking liquid chap stick! The arome was almost as bad as the taste, the appearance was sickening, but a decent palateIts a sad day when i rather drink Canadian than another beer. Yuck!
Not bad.  Not really my type of beer and has a weird taste.  Definitely NOT the best beer in Canada, as the local bartender suggested.
Is this beer?  I mean, i thought i was drinking wine.  well, this stuff would be good if i already had many other beers, but for now, its just plain bad.
Fairly good lager with a distinct aftertaste. Dont mind drinking alot of it either.
UPDATED: AUG 8, 2003
This beer is ass, i mean mass produced garbage. You have to really want to get drunk to drink this.  Goes down easier than some beers, such as the dreaded Canadian!
This lager goes down smooth with a good honey brown taste.  It is good to look at and has a nice aroma.  Good job Sleeman (better than that Cream Ale crap!)
This beer goes down easy for a mass produced beer.  It is up on my list and i could drink it all night.  Easy on the palate but a tad bitter
This is not a spectacular beer but when served with a lime, its something different and one of my favs.  Not high up on the quality scale, but good nontheless
UPDATED: JAN 27, 2003
Too bitter for me.  I can understand how some people like it, but its rough on the palate and too thick.
Is this beer or URINE?  This is a perfect example of mass produced beer that is generic in every way to please people that dont know real beer!
